# how/ — Operations (Agent Reference)

## Purpose

`how/` holds operations — the **HOW** of **{{project_name}}**. Missions, sessions, templates, and optionally backlog, pipelines, and skills.

## Subdirectories

| Folder | Purpose | Status |
|--------|---------|--------|
| `missions/` | Build plans for multi-session work | Required |
| `sessions/` | Session tracking and audit trail | Required |
| `templates/` | Reusable templates for all content types | Required |

Add operational subdirectories as needed (e.g., `backlog/`, `campaigns/`, `pipelines/`, `skills/`).

## Working Rules

- All files follow `type_descriptive_name.md` (underscores only, never hyphens)
- Sessions go in `sessions/active/` while open, then archive to `sessions/history/YYYY-MM/`
- Missions are multi-session plans — decompose large tasks into missions before starting

## Load/Skip Decision

**Load when**: Orienting on operational systems or deciding which subdirectory to work in.
**Skip when**: Already know the target subdirectory — go directly to its AGENTS.md.

